  18. /* A concurrent dictionary data structure implemented as skip lists. See
  19.    implementation for much more detail. */

  21. /* Keys and associated data are natural-width integers (type [uintnat]).
  22.    Key values 0 and uintnat_max are reserved for internal use; do not use.
  23.    Pointers can be used too, modulo conversion to [uintnat]. */

  58. /* Initialize a skip list */
  59. extern void caml_lf_skiplist_init(struct lf_skiplist *sk);

  61. /* Search a skip list.
  62.    If [key] is found, store associated data in [*data] and return 1.
  63.    If [key] is not found, return 0 and leave [*data] unchanged. */
  64. extern int caml_lf_skiplist_find(struct lf_skiplist *sk, uintnat key,
  65.                                  /*out*/ uintnat *data);

  67. /* Search the entry of the skip list that has the largest key less than
  68.    or equal to [k].
  69.    If such an entry exists, store its key in [*key], the associated data in
  70.    [*data], and return 1.
  71.    If no such entry exists (all keys in the skip list are strictly greater
  72.    than [k]), return 0 and leave [*key] and [*data] unchanged. */
  73. extern int caml_lf_skiplist_find_below(struct lf_skiplist *sk, uintnat k,
  74.                                        /*out*/ uintnat *key,
  75.                                        /*out*/ uintnat *data);
  76. /* Insertion in a skip list. [key] must be between 1 and UINTNAT_MAX-1.
  77.    If [key] was already there, change the associated data and return 1.
  78.    If [key] was not there, insert new [key, data] binding and return 0. */
  79. extern int caml_lf_skiplist_insert(struct lf_skiplist *sk, uintnat key,
  80.                                    uintnat data);

  82. /* Deletion in a skip list.
  83.    If [key] was there, remove it and return 1.
  84.    If [key] was not there, leave the skip list unchanged and return 0. */
  85. extern int caml_lf_skiplist_remove(struct lf_skiplist *sk, uintnat key);

  87. /* This must only be called by a single domain during a stop-the world
  88.     protected by global barriers. */
  89. extern void caml_lf_skiplist_free_garbage(struct lf_skiplist *sk);

  96. ‌#define LF_SK_EXTRACT(from, mark_to, ptr_to)                                   \
  97.   {                                                                            \
  98.     uintptr_t tmp = (uintptr_t)atomic_load_acquire(&(from));                   \
  99.     mark_to = LF_SK_IS_MARKED(tmp);                                            \
  100.     ptr_to = LF_SK_UNMARK(tmp);                          \
  101.   }

  103. /* Iterate over a skip list, in increasing order of keys.
  104.    [var] designates the current element.
  105.    [action] can refer to [var->key] and [var->data].
  106.    [action] can safely remove the current element, i.e. call
  107.    [caml_skiplist_remove] on [var->key].  The traversal will
  108.    continue with the skiplist element following the removed element.
  109.    Other operations performed over the skiplist during its traversal have
  110.    unspecified effects on the traversal. */

  112. ‌#define FOREACH_LF_SKIPLIST_ELEMENT(var, sk, action)                           \
  113.   {                                                                            \
  114.     struct lf_skipcell *var, *caml__next;                                      \
  115.     int caml__marked;                                                          \
  116.     var = (sk)->head->forward[0];                                              \
  117.     while (var != (sk)->tail) {                                                \
  118.       LF_SK_EXTRACT(var->forward[0], caml__marked, caml__next);                \
  119.       if (!caml__marked) {                                                     \
  120.         action;                                                                \
  121.       }                                                                        \
  122.       var = caml__next;                                                        \
  123.     }                                                                          \
  124.   }
